I'd really prefer not to add an extra UUID field/header. We've been gradually phasing out pid.getUuid() in favor of pid.getId(), since the former just calls the latter, and neither necessarily returns a UUID. You can also get the ID/UUID portion back from the PID field, which it looks like you were doing before in DestroyedMsgProcessor. Was there a reason you needed to switch? I'd suggest:
String binaryPidId = (String) in.getHeader(CdrBinaryPidId);
PID binaryPid = PIDs.get(binaryPidId);
String binaryId = binaryPid.getId();

